                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            We all would agree on one thing– that the pandemic demolished all boundaries between work and home. Our homes became our places of work, and the idea of ‘coming back home’ to relax had long vanished. We were in front of our screens throughout the day, attending meetings, completing projects and assignments and whatnot. It was a nightmare. Eventually, we became used to it (not entirely, though ;) 
                            <br>
                            Anything in excess is detrimental to our well-being- be it excess of rest or excess of work. Our only aim in this blog is to make you realise that it is okay to rest, take a break and be kind to yourself. Working hard doesn’t necessarily mean pushing yourself to a state of burnout where you don’t even have the energy to live life. 

                        </p>

                       
