                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">1. <u>Plan your Schedule in Advance


                        </u>

                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            With high workload levels, it is always better to plan your tasks in your daily schedule. Scheduling your tasks in advance would give you clarity on what tasks you need to complete for each day. It is essential to plan your breaks in your schedule as well. Often unforeseen circumstances can disrupt our planned schedule, so keeping buffer time and empty slots in your schedule is necessary. You can utilise these empty slots when other unexpected commitments arise.

                        
                        </p>
<div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2FWork_from_home.jpg?alt=media&token=be7fb9a5-9a95-4eb4-98d0-36fce4327241" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
<br>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">2.<u> Designate ‘No-Work’ Slots 


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            It is crucial to plan your ‘no work’ time as well. Be as sincere about your ‘no work’ time as you are about your work. This time is solely meant for you to relax and rewind from all the work you have done throughout the day. These ‘no work’ slots can be afternoon naps or a few free hours in the early morning or late evening. You can schedule these slots at your convenience. 

                        </p>

                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2F2111.i301.013.S.m004.c13.Balancing%20in%20life%20isometric%20composition.jpg?alt=media&token=7dd12639-786e-41f0-980a-7696482eedc5" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
<br>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">3.<u> Take out Time for your Interests 



                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Despite your heavy schedule and workload, try taking out some time for the things you genuinely enjoy doing. You should do things you ought to do and the things you like to do. Taking time out to pursue your hobbies daily would give you the much-needed serotonin boost. For instance, despite my workload, I ensure to watch an episode of a K-drama each day to de-stress and keep myself happy. 

                        </p>

                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2F2110.i605.003.S.m005.c12.life%20balance%20illustration.jpg?alt=media&token=3775f6d0-dd7b-4c18-b66f-c89565453cef" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">4.<u> Recharge During Weekends 

                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Try completing your tasks during weekdays and keep the weekends free for you to rejuvenate yourself. If work arises during the weekends, see if it’s possible to schedule it for the next week. The weekends are a holiday for a reason, and you must make utmost use of them to give yourself a detox break from work. 

                        </p>
                        

                        <div class="row" >
                          <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                              <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2FLandscape%20of%20summer%20city%20park%20with%20happy%20people%20on%20picnic.jpg?alt=media&token=885f2376-3075-4817-83a3-78e4d2570b77" >
                          </div>
                          </div>
                      <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">5.<u> Be Assertive (Learn to Say ‘No’)




                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Being assertive and learning to politely say “No” to extra tasks when you already have a lot on your plate is a necessary skill you need to develop. Yes, I call it a skill because some people struggle to say “No” and end up doing tasks that were not assigned to them. So learn to negotiate with your peers and supervisors (healthily and positively). You can use polite yet affirmative statements like, “I would love to help, but I’m sorry. I’m occupied with my share of work at the moment. I hope you understand.”

                        </p>
                        
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">6.<u>Unplug from All Devices 




                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Since the pandemic, most of us have been heavily occupied with digital devices. We spend our entire day in front of our phone and laptop screens. This causes quite a bit of load on our physical and mental health. So be mindful to shut down all your systems and devices for a few hours in your day. If you have worked throughout the day, you can ensure that you keep all devices at bay and unwind at night. 

                        </p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2Fna_january_47.jpg?alt=media&token=d661024d-12f5-4435-890d-bd17f286778c" >
                            </div>
                            </div>

  <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">7.<u> Connect with Family and Friends


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            It is vital to stay connected to your close social networks, such as your close family members and friends. Talk to your family and friends and share things with them. You can ask how their day was and tell them how was yours. Such interaction is necessary to feel connected and secure. You can video call your friends or family if they stay far away from you and catch up on life with them. 
                        </p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2F4010210.jpg?alt=media&token=38ea8d24-121f-4a6c-add2-fa7b60483413" >
                            </div>
                            </div>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">8.<u> Delegate Work 



                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            While working in a team or group, ensure to delegate work among team members instead of taking the load of the work on yourself. Delegation of work would ensure that no one person feels burdened or pressured. Sharing the load of tasks makes it easier to complete, leaving everyone some spare time to relax. 
</p>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">9.<u> Ascertain your Working Capacity


                        </u>
                        </H3>
                        
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            It is crucial to ascertain how much workload you can handle. Don’t sign up for extra tasks, projects or courses if you feel your current workload is exhausting. We often sign up for things simply because our peers are doing so. Everyone has a different working capacity and different priorities. So, suit your convenience and be clear about how much work you can handle without burning yourself out. 
</p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Flifebalanceblog%2F5301618.jpg?alt=media&token=1ec9fe92-0c2e-42d2-89ee-59a9fe479428" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">10.<u> Seek Peer Support 



                        </u>
                        </H3>
                       
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Often tasks take up more of our time because we find them challenging to do all alone and struggle with them. In such cases, working in tandem with your peers is best. You can plan group study or project sessions where each individual can work on their individual tasks and also help each other out when needed. Relying on a good peer support system ensures that you don’t get burdened with tasks all alone. 
<br>
We hope these tips help you in finding your work-life balance. Take care and Stay Safe!
</p>
                      




